            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_8484.xml">Charles</ref> and <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_8485.xml">Alfred Morrison</ref> and <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_8486.xml">Julian Goldsmid</ref>; see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12546.xml">letter to James Caird, 24 March 1880</ref> and n. 3.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_8487.xml">John Mulholland</ref> was MP for Downpatrick.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">For Torbitt’s hope about competing successfully with the United States ‘in the production of beef, pork, butter, and cheese’, see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 27, enclosure to <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12322.xml">letter from James Torbitt, 15 November 1879</ref>.</note>
